Peter Dada,  Akure There was a pandemonium at the Oja Oba area of Akure,  Ondo State, on Sunday as some traders engaged the followers of a masquerader in a free-for-all. It was gathered that one of the followers of the masquerader was allegedly stabbed by a trader during the clash. The cause of the clash was unknown as at the time of filling this report. An eyewitness said there were sounds of gunshots during the clash, adding that the person allegedly stabbed died. Many traders and residents around the popular Oba Adesida Road were said to have ran for safety, while motorists took alternative routes to their destinations. The state Police Public Relations Officer,  Mr Tee-Leo Ikoro, confirmed the incident but said no life was lost. “When the soldiers attached Operation Smile  patrol got to area,  all the hoodlums were dispersed. But investigation has commenced to know the cause of the clash, ‘ he said. Copyright PUNCH.
